The paper deals with the task of preference elicitation, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed algorithm, Choice Perceptron, is based on a Perceptron-like approach, which is a well-known technique in machine learning and data science (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the theoretical analysis of the algorithm's performance, which is related to optimization and decision-making (cs.HC). Finally, the empirical evaluation of the algorithm is done on constructive scenarios, which involves generating new objects, and this is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR).
